    "body": "Well, you're running with `--allow-insecure-unlock`, plus expose the rpc interface to the public interface `0.0.0.0`, plus expose `admin, personal`. \r\nI suspect what's happening is that someone on the internet does RPC calls to set your miner address to their address, so they get the rewards. It's a useless attack, since you're not on mainnet, but I guess the attacker-scripts doesn't bother to check if it's worthwhile to do it, they just do it. \r\n\r\nYou should see some info about it in the logs, like `Served miner.setCoinbaseBase` (or whatever method they used)",
