    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Typical recommendations: \r\n- Don't unlock accounts, especially if you also expose RPC. Unlocking is inherently _insecure_ hence the hint in the switch to explicitly do it anyway: `insecure-unlock`. \r\n- Don't expose your node RPC towards the internet: don't set `0.0.0.0` as the interface. use localhost instead, and if you want to interact with it, you set up an ssh tunnel `ssh -L 8545:localhost:8545 user@machine`, then you can interact with `localhost:8545` at the machine you made the connection from. \r\n\r\n",
